The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Taufel clinic in city today

A STAFF REPORTER 

Calcutta: Australian Simon Taufel will hold a clinic for local umpires at the CAB on Monday. Taufel, a three-time ICC Umpire of the Year award-winner, will be the neutral umpire for the opening ODI between India and Sri Lanka at the Eden on Thursday. 

The players will reach the city on Tuesday. 

Meanwhile, for the first time, CAB is inviting Indian women cricketers to watch the match. An invitation letter has already been sent to India vice-captain Jhulan Goswami, a CAB official said on Sunday. 

Invitations have also been sent to former captains Mansur Ali Khan Pataudi, Sunil Gavaskar and Kapil Dev. 




